article.headline: Nittany Lions upend top-10 Buckeyes
article.linkText: Harris' 22 sends Penn State over Ohio State
article.story:
STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Jen Harris couldn't find the words to
describe her second-half outburst.

Harris scored 18 of her career-high 22 points in the second half
to lead Penn State to a 69-62 upset of Ohio State (No. 7 ESPN/USA Today; No. 9 AP) on Thursday
night.

Harris scored 13 points, including 10 straight, during a 20-5
run that gave the Lady Lions (6-5) a 38-29 lead with 16:32 left.

"I'm in it and I have no idea what's going on," Harris said.
"There's nothing on my mind except happiness, and we're up and
we're winning. Adrenaline's pumping, you're just in it. Everybody's
in it, everybody's on top of their game."

Tanisha Wright added 10 of her 22 points in the final 15 minutes
to stretch Penn State's lead to as many as 12 with 5:40 remaining.

Ohio State (11-2) got 20 points from Jessica Davenport,
including 16 in the second half, and 18 from Brandie Hoskins. But
the Big Ten's best ball-control team -- a 1.50 assists-to-turnovers
ratio entering the game -- couldn't overcome 17 turnovers and seven
blocked shots.

Penn State coach Rene Portland credited the team's defensive
effort in the win.

"We changed our zone, who was playing what in coverage,"
Portland said. "We've never practiced it and (the players) went
out and did it, and I think that confused Ohio State. They thought
we were showing some things and we really just made a little tweak
in what we were doing defensively."

Guard Jess Strom added 12 rebounds and nine assists for Penn
State.

Ohio State coach Jim Foster said it was Penn State's defense
that humbled his Buckeyes, who had their eight-game winning streak
snapped.

"I think if there's one thing you can look at on a stat sheet,
if there's any kind of things that jump out at you ... that should
just totally, totally embarrass our team is that Jess Strom got 12
rebounds," Foster said. "To her credit, she does it on a day when
she can't throw the ball in the ocean.

"She found a way to help her basketball team, she found a way
to do the little things that are necessary to win a basketball
game."
